GMATWiz - Wednesday proof: build
=================================
This file verifies the source tree builds. The command used is exactly what
`./run` uses to build before launching:

    ./ninja pylib qt

Run below was INCREMENTAL (the tree was already built this session), so ninja
reports "up to date" / a sub-second finish. That proves the graph is consistent
and nothing is broken, but it is not a from-scratch build.

For the graded "clean-build recording", do a from-scratch build on camera:

    cd anki-fork
    rm -rf out            # wipe all build outputs
    ./tools/install-n2    # (first time only) fetch the ninja build tool
    ./run                 # runs `./ninja pylib qt` from clean, then launches

A from-scratch build compiles the Rust engine (rslib), the Python wheels, and
the SvelteKit UI, and typically takes ~10-20 min on a laptop. See
proof/RECORDING_GUIDE.md.

